Package stars

Class StudentProgram

java.lang.Object
stars.StudentProgram
public class StudentProgram
extends java.lang.Object
A class that represents the program that a student will use during add/drop period. This class serves as a boundary class between the user and the databases of the MySTARS system.
Since:
10/11/2020
Version:
1.0.0
Author:
Lucius Lee, Lai Ming Hui

    • setCurrentStudent

      public void setCurrentStudent​(Student_details student)
      Set the current user's Student_details object. When set, all program operations such as add, drop will be performed for this specified student.
      Parameters:
      student - The specified student to be the current user.

    • run

      public void run​(Student_details student)
      Method called by host application to run this instance of the student program.
      Parameters:
      student - Student_details object associated with the current user of the program.

    • promptForIndexCode

      private Index_details promptForIndexCode​(java.lang.String message)
      Prompts the user for an index code. This method will loop until a valid index code is entered, or the user enters 0, whereby this method will return null.
      Parameters:
      message - The message to prompt the user before input.
      Returns:
      The Index_detail object with the input index code from the current database, or null if such an object cannot be found.

    • promptYesNo

      private boolean promptYesNo​(java.lang.String message)
      Prompts the user for a Y/N input. This method will loop until the user enters a "Y", "y", "N" or "n". If the user enters "Y" or"y", the method returns true. If the user enters "N" or "n", the method returns false.
      Parameters:
      message - The message to prompt the user before input.
      Returns:
      True if the user input "Y" or "y", false if the user input "N" or "n".

    • run_AddIndex

      private void run_AddIndex()
      Method implementing the "Add" function for the student program. This methods prompts the user for an index code, then attempts to add register the current user into the index specified.

    • run_DropIndex

      private void run_DropIndex()
      Method implementing the "Drop" function for the student program. This methods will prompt the user for an index code, then attempts to drop the index specified for the current user.

    • run_CheckVacancies

      private void run_CheckVacancies()
      Method implementing the "Check vacancies" fucntion for the student program. This method prompts the user for an index code, the prints out the index's vacancies.

    • run_ChangeIndex

      private void run_ChangeIndex()
      Method implementing the "Change index" function for the student program. This method prompts the user for two indexes: the first index should be one that the user has registered for, and the other is an index under the same course that the user has not registered or in the waitlist for. This method will then attempt to exchange the two indexes.

    • run_SwapIndex

      private void run_SwapIndex()
      Method implementing the "Swap index" function of the student program. This method will prompt the current user for the index to swap, and then prompts the index and credentials of the other student. If the credentials given are correct and the indexes are valid and already registered by both students, this method will swap their indexes.

    • run_PrintIndex

      private void run_PrintIndex()
      Method implementing the print index function of the student program. This method will prompt the user for the index to print, and then print the index's details if the specified index is valid.

    • addIndex

      private void addIndex​(java.lang.String indexCode)
      Method to register a an index for a student. If the index has vacancies, the student is added to it. If the index has no more vacancies, the student is put into the waitlist instead.
      Parameters:
      indexCode - The specified index code of the index to register.

    • dropIndex

      private void dropIndex​(java.lang.String indexCode)
      Method to drop an index from a student's registration. This method will drop the index from a student's registration if it exist and the student is registered in it. If there are any students waiting for this index, students will be added from the wait list to the registered list in firstin first out order.
      Parameters:
      indexCode - The specified code of the index to drop.

    • CheckVacancies

      private void CheckVacancies​(java.lang.String indexCode)
      Method to check the vacancies of a course index
      Parameters:
      indexCode - The code of the index to check

    • changeCourseIndex

      private void changeCourseIndex​(java.lang.String oldindex, java.lang.String newindex)
      Change the index specified in old index with the index specified in new index.
      Parameters:
      oldindex - The code of the index registered by the user to be changed.
      newindex - The code of the index to be changed with.

    • SwapIndex

      private void SwapIndex​(java.lang.String userindex, Student_details newstudent, java.lang.String stuindex)
      Method to swap the indexes between the current user and the student specified in newstudent. If the index codes specified are valid, the indexes will be swapped and a notification email will be send to the current user and CCed to the swapping student. Otherwise no swapping will happen and no email is sent. This method only performs swapping. Credentials entry is implemented in run_swapIndex().
      Parameters:
      userindex - The code of the index registered by the user to be swapped.
      newstudent - The Student_details object of the swapping student.
      stuindex - The code of the index registered by the swapping student to be swapped with.

    • notifySwapSuccessful

      private void notifySwapSuccessful​(Student_details student1, java.lang.String index1, Student_details student2, java.lang.String index2)
      Sends a notifcation to the specified students that their index swapping is successful. This method does not check if the indexes has actually been swapped or registered. This method only creates the notifications and sends them to the specified students.
      Parameters:
      student1 - The first student doing the swap
      index1 - The index of the first student that is to be swapped
      student2 - The second student doing the swap with student1
      index2 - The index of student2 that is to be swapped with index1.

    • addStudentIndexRegistered

      private void addStudentIndexRegistered​(Student_details student, Index_details index)
      Adds the specified student to the specified index. This method does does nothing if the student is already registered in the index or the index has no more vacancies. This method also updates the student's AU according to the index's AU. If the index is in the student's waitlist, this method removes the index from the waitlist.
      Parameters:
      student - The sepcified student
      index - THe specified index

    • addStudentIndexWaitlist

      private void addStudentIndexWaitlist​(Student_details student, Index_details index)
      Adds the specified student to the specified index's waitlist. This method does does nothing if the student is already registered or waiting for the index. This method also updates the student's AU according to the index's AU.
      Parameters:
      student - The sepcified student
      index - THe specified index

    • swapIndex

      private boolean swapIndex​(Student_details student1, Index_details index1, Student_details student2, Index_details index2)
      Swaps a index registered by student1 with a index registered by student2. This method does nothing if: the specified indexes are not in the same course, studen1 is not registered in index1, or student2 is not registered in student2.
      Parameters:
      student1 - The student to initiate the swapping
      index1 - The index registered by student1 to be swapped
      student2 - The student to swap index with
      index2 - The index of student2 to be swapped
      Returns:
      True is the swap is successful, false otherwise
